01:13:07.279 --> 01:13:14.279
You know, I often look at these Treaty settlement processes in the part that we play.

624
01:13:14.279 --> 01:13:24.279
We, as members of Parliament, are here for a small amount of time to try and do the best we can

625
01:13:24.279 --> 01:13:29.279
in what I call a process that's perfectly imperfect.

626
01:13:29.279 --> 01:13:39.279
It's by no means, and as we've heard, I empathise with people saying that the redress is a stretch of the surface.

627
01:13:39.279 --> 01:13:44.279
It's a pittance of actually the wrong doings of the past.

628
01:13:44.279 --> 01:13:50.279
And we see this all over the water, all over the place, back where I'm from, the Karanaki.

629
01:13:50.279 --> 01:13:52.279
We've seen it all there.

630
01:13:52.279 --> 01:14:01.279
And I'm very mindful personally that this process here is about providing a new beginning to rebuild

631
01:14:01.279 --> 01:14:06.279
